1
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,074
Delicious Vegan Sausages, Cheese
and Burgers - Vegusto.co.uk

2
00:00:41,141 --> 00:00:43,609
This is the police!
Open up!

3
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:57,022
Police! Anyone here?

4
00:01:06,232 --> 00:01:08,067
Hey, fella.
Anybody home?

5
00:01:34,894 --> 00:01:38,063
Ma'am, turn around slowly.

6
00:01:48,174 --> 00:01:50,442
Unit 507,
we got a possible homicide.

7
00:01:50,510 --> 00:01:52,444
Requesting backup.

8
00:01:52,512 --> 00:01:56,381
<i>Copy that, 507. Backup is
en route. ETA 10 minutes.</i>

9
00:01:57,750 --> 00:01:59,551
Adrian?

10
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:00,619
Adrian!

11
00:02:14,234 --> 00:02:15,767
Adrian.

12
00:02:43,196 --> 00:02:44,763
Cobbs.

13
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:24,636
Cobbs!

14
00:03:34,314 --> 00:03:36,748
This is Unit 507.
I've got an officer down.

15
00:03:36,816 --> 00:03:38,450
Repeat, officer down.

16
00:03:40,753 --> 00:03:42,888
<i>Copy, 507.
EMS is being notified.</i>

17
00:03:42,956 --> 00:03:45,657
<i>Backup to your location
in five minutes.</i>

18
00:04:17,257 --> 00:04:19,324
It's gonna be so much better
than the city, honey.

19
00:04:19,392 --> 00:04:25,030
You're gonna have sidewalks
to ride your bike on and a yard.

20
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:27,065
You're gonna love it.

21
00:04:28,234 --> 00:04:30,068
I miss Daddy.

22
00:04:31,571 --> 00:04:34,106
I know, honey.

23
00:04:34,173 --> 00:04:36,108
But you're gonna be
so much happier here.

24
00:04:36,175 --> 00:04:38,610
I promise. You'll see.

25
00:05:05,538 --> 00:05:06,938
There they are!

26
00:05:07,006 --> 00:05:08,307
- Hi.
- Hi.

27
00:05:08,374 --> 00:05:09,841
You must be Claire.

28
00:05:09,909 --> 00:05:11,576
Your mommy's told me
a lot about you,

29
00:05:11,644 --> 00:05:13,679
so I brought you something
very special from our office

30
00:05:13,746 --> 00:05:14,946
Ta-da!

31
00:05:17,784 --> 00:05:21,153
I'm sorry. She's still not 100%
about this whole moving thing.

32
00:05:21,220 --> 00:05:24,823
That's all right. She will be
when she sees her new room.

33
00:05:26,626 --> 00:05:27,926
Come on. Let's go inside.

34
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:33,799
Welcome home.

35
00:05:38,805 --> 00:05:42,174
What do you think, hmm?
I mean, I know it's not perfect,

36
00:05:42,241 --> 00:05:44,343
but I think with a little bit
of work, it'll be great.

37
00:05:44,410 --> 00:05:46,678
Well, you know, there was
a lot of interest in this house,

38
00:05:46,746 --> 00:05:48,847
mostly from
real estate speculators,

39
00:05:48,915 --> 00:05:51,850
but I felt that
it needed a family.

40
00:05:53,986 --> 00:05:55,120
You like it?

41
00:05:57,023 --> 00:05:58,924
Did something happen here?

42
00:05:58,991 --> 00:06:00,025
What?

43
00:06:00,093 --> 00:06:02,527
Well, it's an old house.

44
00:06:02,595 --> 00:06:06,131
It's got a lot of history,
but nothing too bad.

45
00:06:06,199 --> 00:06:08,333
- There you go.
- Oh, thanks.

46
00:06:08,401 --> 00:06:11,103
Those are for the front door,
the back door, and the garage.

47
00:06:11,170 --> 00:06:12,637
I'm right in town.

48
00:06:12,705 --> 00:06:14,573
Call me if you need
anything at all.

49
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:16,541
- What is this?
- That's for the keys.

50
00:06:16,609 --> 00:06:18,210
Oh, okay.

51
00:06:20,146 --> 00:06:21,413
You keep that.

52
00:06:21,481 --> 00:06:23,048
Thank you.

53
00:08:04,417 --> 00:08:05,417
Oh.

54
00:08:24,737 --> 00:08:27,172
"Lilith."

55
00:08:32,311 --> 00:08:34,212
What's that?

56
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:35,981
What's what?

57
00:08:36,048 --> 00:08:37,182
Claire.

58
00:08:39,418 --> 00:08:41,152
Please, Mommy, can I keep her?

59
00:08:41,220 --> 00:08:43,755
But you have so many other dolls
already, honey.

60
00:08:43,823 --> 00:08:46,992
But I want this one.

61
00:08:47,059 --> 00:08:50,095
I think that one probably
belongs to somebody else.

62
00:08:50,162 --> 00:08:52,130
Finders keepers.

63
00:08:54,734 --> 00:08:58,203
Fine, but you have
to let me wash it first.

64
00:08:58,271 --> 00:08:59,271
Come on.

65
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:03,708
All right, keep unpacking.

66
00:09:03,776 --> 00:09:05,210
Okay.

67
00:09:16,255 --> 00:09:18,723
Everything's going pretty well.

68
00:09:18,791 --> 00:09:23,662
I mean, she's not
super excited, but...

69
00:09:23,729 --> 00:09:25,597
What's going on with you?

70
00:09:25,665 --> 00:09:27,132
<i>Same-old, same-old.
Grading papers.</i>

71
00:09:27,199 --> 00:09:28,833
<i>Everything okay with the move?</i>

72
00:09:28,901 --> 00:09:31,102
Yeah. You know what?

73
00:09:31,170 --> 00:09:34,673
Thanks so much for helping me
with that article.

74
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:36,575
It's hard to imagine
there's actually people

75
00:09:36,642 --> 00:09:39,878
who believe this stuff is real.

76
00:09:39,946 --> 00:09:42,581
Sometimes it's easier to rely on
a supernatural explanation

77
00:09:42,648 --> 00:09:45,483
rather than confronting
the truth.

78
00:09:45,551 --> 00:09:47,652
So what are you gonna do now?

79
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:50,155
Well, I'm gonna talk
to some of the local papers,

80
00:09:50,222 --> 00:09:52,390
but I really just want
to take some time

81
00:09:52,458 --> 00:09:55,160
and work on my book
and focus on Claire.

82
00:09:55,227 --> 00:09:56,595
<i>Good.</i>

83
00:09:56,662 --> 00:09:58,797
It's much bigger
than our old apartment.

84
00:09:58,864 --> 00:10:01,533
- Claire?
- <i>Everything okay?</i>

85
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:03,969
You know what? I'm gonna go.
I'll call you later?

86
00:10:04,036 --> 00:10:06,438
Okay, honey.
Good luck with the unpacking.

87
00:10:06,505 --> 00:10:09,140
Thanks.

88
00:10:09,208 --> 00:10:12,777
And I have some friends for you
in one of these boxes.

89
00:10:12,845 --> 00:10:17,482
Tomorrow I have to go
to a new school with new kids.

90
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:20,719
I'm scared.

91
00:10:22,788 --> 00:10:27,459
I hope they're nice,
not mean like some kids.

92
00:10:27,526 --> 00:10:30,261
What if they don't like me?

93
00:10:32,498 --> 00:10:35,000
What if they don't need
any new friends?

94
00:10:39,739 --> 00:10:40,972
Hey.

95
00:10:45,711 --> 00:10:47,145
I know it's hard.

96
00:10:49,248 --> 00:10:54,653
You're gonna do great.

97
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:56,554
I promise.

98
00:10:56,622 --> 00:10:58,790
Can I sleep with the light on?

99
00:10:58,858 --> 00:11:01,526
Aren't you forgetting something?

100
00:11:01,594 --> 00:11:03,094
Mom.

101
00:11:03,162 --> 00:11:04,229
Come on.

102
00:11:04,296 --> 00:11:06,164
Okay.

103
00:11:06,232 --> 00:11:09,167
Now I lay me down to sleep,

104
00:11:09,235 --> 00:11:12,904
I pray the Lord
my soul to keep.

105
00:11:12,972 --> 00:11:17,075
If I should die before I wake,

106
00:11:17,143 --> 00:11:20,679
I pray the Lord
my soul to take.

107
00:11:26,485 --> 00:11:29,020
- 3 times 3?
- Nine.

108
00:11:29,088 --> 00:11:31,356
- 3 times 4?
- 12.

109
00:11:31,424 --> 00:11:33,892
- 3 times 5?
- 15.

110
00:11:33,959 --> 00:11:37,328
3 times 6?

111
00:11:37,396 --> 00:11:39,464
Claire?

112
00:11:39,532 --> 00:11:41,700
Are you paying attention?

113
00:11:41,767 --> 00:11:44,302
18.

114
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:46,304
Very good.

115
00:11:46,372 --> 00:11:48,873
- 3 times 7?
- 21.

116
00:11:50,910 --> 00:11:53,144
Hey, did you really move
into the bad house?

117
00:11:53,212 --> 00:11:54,979
I heard it's haunted.

118
00:11:55,047 --> 00:11:56,581
Stop it.

119
00:11:56,649 --> 00:11:58,817
You moved into the bad house?

120
00:11:58,884 --> 00:12:00,652
Stop it.

121
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:01,853
It's gonna get you.

122
00:12:01,921 --> 00:12:06,958
♪ It's gonna get you ♪

123
00:12:07,026 --> 00:12:08,993
- ♪ It's gonna get you ♪
- Hey!

124
00:12:09,061 --> 00:12:11,396
Stop it!

125
00:12:52,371 --> 00:12:53,872
Hello?

126
00:13:01,547 --> 00:13:04,916
Hello?

127
00:13:11,190 --> 00:13:12,590
Oh, my God!

128
00:13:12,658 --> 00:13:14,926
- The door was open.
- Can I help you?

129
00:13:14,994 --> 00:13:17,162
I'm Janine, your new neighbor.

130
00:13:17,229 --> 00:13:18,963
Alyson.

131
00:13:19,031 --> 00:13:21,866
I thought this place
was gonna... Oh!

132
00:13:21,934 --> 00:13:23,468
Whoops!

133
00:13:28,007 --> 00:13:30,675
They kept
all the original fixtures.

134
00:13:32,878 --> 00:13:34,646
It's lovely.

135
00:13:34,713 --> 00:13:37,048
Oh, where are my manners?

136
00:13:37,116 --> 00:13:38,283
Sorry they're a bit smushed,

137
00:13:38,350 --> 00:13:40,518
but my cats were
walking on them.

138
00:13:40,586 --> 00:13:43,354
Thank you.

139
00:13:43,422 --> 00:13:45,456
Oh, look.
There's one of them now.

140
00:13:45,524 --> 00:13:48,960
Smokey!

141
00:13:51,096 --> 00:13:52,897
He's my oldest.

142
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:55,900
You have a little girl.

143
00:13:55,968 --> 00:13:58,369
Yeah. Claire. She's nine.

144
00:13:58,437 --> 00:14:01,673
My cats simply adore children.

145
00:14:01,740 --> 00:14:03,474
Oh, that's great.

146
00:14:07,313 --> 00:14:09,113
So if Claire ever wants to come
and play with the kitties,

147
00:14:09,181 --> 00:14:10,548
just send her over.

148
00:14:10,616 --> 00:14:12,317
They would love it.

149
00:14:12,384 --> 00:14:15,320
And if you need anything,
just holler.

150
00:14:15,387 --> 00:14:17,422
- Okay, thank you.
- Bye!

151
00:14:17,489 --> 00:14:19,224
It's nice to meet you.

152
00:14:25,698 --> 00:14:27,131
Wow.

153
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:35,874
Mommy said
it would be better here,

154
00:14:35,941 --> 00:14:37,809
that I'd be happy.

155
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:40,044
She promised.

156
00:14:40,112 --> 00:14:41,779
I thought things
would be different,

157
00:14:41,847 --> 00:14:44,782
that people would be nicer.

158
00:14:44,850 --> 00:14:47,151
But they're not.

159
00:14:47,219 --> 00:14:49,387
They pick on me.

160
00:14:50,856 --> 00:14:52,357
I hate them.

161
00:14:52,424 --> 00:14:55,393
I wish they were dead.

162
00:15:29,995 --> 00:15:34,232
- I won't go back there!
- Claire, you have to!

163
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:35,500
- Stop it.
- No.

164
00:15:35,567 --> 00:15:37,101
- Yes.
- I want to go home.

165
00:15:37,169 --> 00:15:38,603
- We are home.
- No!

166
00:15:38,671 --> 00:15:40,004
You don't scream at me.

167
00:15:40,072 --> 00:15:41,005
No!

168
00:15:41,073 --> 00:15:43,875
Let me go!

169
00:15:55,554 --> 00:15:59,390
♪ They put you in
a wooden box ♪

170
00:15:59,458 --> 00:16:01,559
Claire, honey, I know
you don't want to go to school,

171
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:03,161
but you need to eat.

172
00:16:03,228 --> 00:16:06,531
♪ Cover you up
with dirt and rocks ♪

173
00:16:06,598 --> 00:16:11,235
♪ Don't you laugh
as the hearse goes by ♪

174
00:16:11,303 --> 00:16:15,306
♪ For you may be
the next to die ♪

175
00:16:15,374 --> 00:16:18,810
Claire, honey, didn't you
hear me calling your name?

176
00:16:18,877 --> 00:16:20,478
Claire.

177
00:16:20,546 --> 00:16:22,814
♪ The worms crawl out ♪

178
00:16:22,881 --> 00:16:27,852
♪ They crawl all over
your dirty snout ♪

179
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:29,821
♪ Your chest caves in ♪

180
00:16:29,888 --> 00:16:33,157
Honey, where did you
learn that song?

181
00:16:33,225 --> 00:16:39,097
♪ Your brain turns into
sauerkraut ♪

182
00:17:03,655 --> 00:17:05,390
Sluggo!

183
00:17:05,457 --> 00:17:07,358
Smokey!

184
00:17:07,426 --> 00:17:08,993
Din-dins!

185
00:17:35,621 --> 00:17:39,190
No! No! No! No!

186
00:17:39,258 --> 00:17:43,628
No! No, no, no, no!

187
00:17:48,167 --> 00:17:53,838
Separation and divorce can be
very stressful for a child.

188
00:17:53,906 --> 00:17:57,341
An entire support system's
been torn out from under her.

189
00:17:59,978 --> 00:18:05,316
The future suddenly appears
very uncertain.

190
00:18:05,384 --> 00:18:09,087
The hardest thing is that you're
having to go through this alone.

191
00:18:09,154 --> 00:18:13,491
I just... I don't know what
I'm supposed to do anymore.

192
00:18:13,559 --> 00:18:17,862
I mean, she won't go to school,
and she'll barely eat anything.

193
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:20,364
Her father still lives
in the city?

194
00:18:20,432 --> 00:18:22,500
Yeah.

195
00:18:22,568 --> 00:18:25,136
Returning to the dynamics
of that environment

196
00:18:25,204 --> 00:18:27,138
might be a helpful thing
for her,

197
00:18:27,206 --> 00:18:31,109
even just for a visit.

198
00:18:31,176 --> 00:18:35,480
I'd strongly consider
letting her go back.

199
00:18:37,349 --> 00:18:39,684
Thank you for your time, Doctor.

200
00:18:47,226 --> 00:18:50,495
The subject exhibits traits
I've seen in similar cases

201
00:18:50,562 --> 00:18:53,164
of callous,
unemotional children.

202
00:18:54,867 --> 00:18:58,069
Distinctive lack of remorse
and empathy.

203
00:19:00,939 --> 00:19:02,974
Further study will be required

204
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:06,611
before I can determine
the presence of psychopathy.

205
00:19:17,256 --> 00:19:19,423
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

206
00:19:29,234 --> 00:19:31,169
You're not even gonna touch
your ice cream?

207
00:19:36,141 --> 00:19:39,143
Fine. Then I will.

208
00:19:39,211 --> 00:19:42,346
I wanna go home.

209
00:19:44,449 --> 00:19:46,484
Honey, this is our home now.

210
00:19:46,552 --> 00:19:50,688
Why? 'Cause you and Daddy
can't get along?

211
00:19:50,756 --> 00:19:52,890
It's a lot more complicated
than that, sweetie.

212
00:19:52,958 --> 00:19:55,226
It's your fault.

213
00:19:57,829 --> 00:19:59,597
Claire...

214
00:19:59,665 --> 00:20:02,233
You're always so busy
with your stupid writing.

215
00:20:02,301 --> 00:20:04,735
No wonder he hates you.

216
00:20:08,740 --> 00:20:10,841
I'm gonna go take care
of the check.

217
00:20:16,715 --> 00:20:17,815
What have you got there?

218
00:20:17,883 --> 00:20:19,850
Give her back.

219
00:20:19,918 --> 00:20:22,086
A pretty girl like you
should have a nice, new doll,

220
00:20:22,154 --> 00:20:24,021
not an ugly, old one
like this.

221
00:20:24,089 --> 00:20:26,090
- She's not ugly.
- Well, look at her.

222
00:20:26,158 --> 00:20:27,592
She's practically falling apart.

223
00:20:27,659 --> 00:20:29,227
I tell you what.

224
00:20:29,294 --> 00:20:31,529
I bet I have a new one
in the back room.

225
00:20:31,597 --> 00:20:32,997
Why don't we throw this one
away, and I'll go get her?

226
00:20:33,065 --> 00:20:35,066
Give her back!

227
00:20:35,133 --> 00:20:36,534
Claire!

228
00:20:37,803 --> 00:20:39,203
I am so sorry.

229
00:20:41,306 --> 00:20:43,541
What is wrong... Claire!

230
00:20:43,609 --> 00:20:44,742
I'm sorry.

231
00:20:52,851 --> 00:20:54,952
I think we should
talk about this, don't you?

232
00:20:56,855 --> 00:20:58,823
She's a murderer!

233
00:20:58,890 --> 00:21:01,792
- What are you talking about?
- Your daughter!

234
00:21:01,860 --> 00:21:03,394
I don't... What?

235
00:21:03,462 --> 00:21:06,397
A child trampled through
my garden last night.

236
00:21:06,465 --> 00:21:07,965
Janine...

237
00:21:08,033 --> 00:21:10,067
I saw the way
she looked at them.

238
00:21:10,135 --> 00:21:13,137
My babies wouldn't hurt anybody,
and now they're dead,

239
00:21:13,205 --> 00:21:14,805
and she killed them!

240
00:21:14,873 --> 00:21:16,874
Okay, well, I'm sorry,
but I can assure you

241
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:20,177
that my daughter had absolutely
nothing to do with your cats.

242
00:21:20,245 --> 00:21:22,146
Excuse me.

243
00:21:41,967 --> 00:21:43,934
Good night, Rose.

244
00:21:44,002 --> 00:21:45,069
Good night, Hank.

245
00:21:54,313 --> 00:21:55,780
Someone there?

246
00:23:35,313 --> 00:23:37,748
- Hey, Daddy.
- It's Daddy's little girl.

247
00:23:37,816 --> 00:23:40,317
Oh, my God, I've missed you.

248
00:23:40,385 --> 00:23:43,320
Bedtime is at 8:30
and no sugar after 6:00.

249
00:23:43,388 --> 00:23:46,090
Yeah, I know.
I've done this before.

250
00:23:46,158 --> 00:23:47,758
Just keep an eye on her, okay?

251
00:23:47,826 --> 00:23:49,660
Ready to go, sweetheart?

252
00:23:52,097 --> 00:23:55,566
Okay, you keep warm, all right?

253
00:24:01,807 --> 00:24:03,474
I love you.

254
00:24:08,013 --> 00:24:12,116
Well, that's a nice house.
How much did you put down?

255
00:24:12,184 --> 00:24:13,951
Don't.

256
00:24:14,019 --> 00:24:16,320
I bet you could get some
good money if you flipped it.

257
00:24:16,388 --> 00:24:18,522
Jonathan, please.

258
00:24:18,590 --> 00:24:21,325
There's a unit that opened up
two floors down from me.

259
00:24:21,393 --> 00:24:24,528
Earl even said
he'd waive the deposit.

260
00:24:24,596 --> 00:24:28,032
Look, just take care of her,
okay?

261
00:24:28,099 --> 00:24:29,667
Okay.

262
00:24:53,992 --> 00:24:56,293
Looks like there's a leak
in one of your fittings.

263
00:24:56,361 --> 00:24:58,262
There's something else.

264
00:25:03,602 --> 00:25:05,803
- What's that?
- You know these people?

265
00:25:05,871 --> 00:25:08,272
No.

266
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:11,108
No, they must be the people
that used to live here.

267
00:25:11,176 --> 00:25:12,977
That looks like
a muñeca quitapena.

268
00:25:13,044 --> 00:25:14,411
A what?

269
00:25:14,479 --> 00:25:16,380
Muñeca quitapena.
The doll.

270
00:25:16,448 --> 00:25:18,415
You don't see them here
in the States much.

271
00:25:18,483 --> 00:25:20,751
They're not usually that big.

272
00:25:20,819 --> 00:25:22,720
My daughter actually
found this in the house.

273
00:25:22,787 --> 00:25:24,555
She's gotten
pretty attached to it.

274
00:25:24,623 --> 00:25:27,124
Bad luck to find
someone else's muñeca.

275
00:26:02,127 --> 00:26:03,928
"Local family found slain."

276
00:26:37,562 --> 00:26:41,732
Zachary, this nice lady is gonna
ask you some questions, okay?

277
00:26:44,202 --> 00:26:45,869
Hi.

278
00:26:45,937 --> 00:26:47,805
I'll be right outside.

279
00:27:01,886 --> 00:27:03,854
Do you mind if I sit down?

280
00:27:20,205 --> 00:27:22,606
I'm Alyson Simon.

281
00:27:22,674 --> 00:27:26,944
I recently moved into
your old house.

282
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:33,117
And I have a little girl
who's nine,

283
00:27:33,184 --> 00:27:37,388
just about the same age you were
when you lived there.

284
00:27:40,058 --> 00:27:42,960
She found your doll.

285
00:27:46,731 --> 00:27:49,533
Do you remember your doll?

286
00:28:04,849 --> 00:28:07,618
She's grown
really attached to it.

287
00:28:10,989 --> 00:28:14,591
Can you tell me why you did it,
Zachary?

288
00:28:14,659 --> 00:28:17,361
Why'd you kill your family?

289
00:28:17,429 --> 00:28:19,430
Was it...

290
00:28:19,497 --> 00:28:23,200
Was it the house?

291
00:28:23,268 --> 00:28:26,904
Was it something in the house?

292
00:28:31,309 --> 00:28:33,143
Zachary.

293
00:28:34,446 --> 00:28:35,512
Zachary!

294
00:28:35,580 --> 00:28:37,815
It's time to go.

295
00:28:37,882 --> 00:28:39,516
No, I just need one more minute.

296
00:28:39,584 --> 00:28:42,086
He's not gonna tell you
anything.

297
00:28:57,702 --> 00:29:03,240
♪ Don't you let
the hearse by ♪

298
00:29:03,308 --> 00:29:06,810
♪ For you may be
the next to die ♪

299
00:29:06,878 --> 00:29:09,546
- Where did you hear that song?
- Ma'am?

300
00:29:09,614 --> 00:29:11,381
Where did you hear that song?

301
00:29:11,449 --> 00:29:13,550
Tell me where you heard
that song!

302
00:29:21,726 --> 00:29:25,763
The kid killed his whole family
and two cops in my house!

303
00:29:25,830 --> 00:29:29,032
We found his picture
under my daughter's floor!

304
00:29:29,100 --> 00:29:32,269
Mrs. Simon, the state civil code
is very clear.

305
00:29:32,337 --> 00:29:35,405
A death in the home
is only a material defect

306
00:29:35,473 --> 00:29:37,775
if it occurs within
three years of the sale.

307
00:29:37,842 --> 00:29:39,777
Material defect?
This isn't a cracked shingle.

308
00:29:39,844 --> 00:29:41,512
It's a multiple homicide!

309
00:29:41,579 --> 00:29:43,113
What do you want me to do?

310
00:29:43,181 --> 00:29:44,882
<i>Tell the bank
that you misrepresented</i>

311
00:29:44,949 --> 00:29:47,351
the condition of the property
and get me my damn money back.

312
00:29:47,418 --> 00:29:50,654
There's no cooling-off period.
This is a done deal.

313
00:29:50,722 --> 00:29:52,856
Then list it. You said there was
a lot of competition.

314
00:29:52,924 --> 00:29:55,659
Sell it to one of the others.

315
00:29:55,727 --> 00:30:00,564
<i>Yeah, well, um...</i>

316
00:30:00,632 --> 00:30:03,567
- There was no one else.
- <i>Listen...</i>

317
00:30:03,635 --> 00:30:06,870
I'm gonna be honest with you.
With the history of this house,

318
00:30:06,938 --> 00:30:10,440
selling it is not gonna be easy,
believe me.

319
00:30:10,508 --> 00:30:13,076
No. You know what?
I'm calling my lawyer.

320
00:30:13,144 --> 00:30:15,846
<i>There's no reason to get...</i>

321
00:30:15,914 --> 00:30:17,214
Damn it.

322
00:30:28,159 --> 00:30:31,328
<i>You knew this would happen.</i>

323
00:30:31,396 --> 00:30:33,397
You were my friend.

324
00:30:33,464 --> 00:30:36,867
<i>And I always will be.</i>

325
00:30:36,935 --> 00:30:38,335
Why?

326
00:30:38,403 --> 00:30:41,872
<i>It's her turn.
She needs me.</i>

327
00:30:44,008 --> 00:30:46,376
<i>You understand, don't you?</i>

328
00:30:46,444 --> 00:30:48,545
<i>Why you have to go?</i>

329
00:30:48,613 --> 00:30:50,380
I'm scared.

330
00:30:50,448 --> 00:30:53,617
<i>Don't be. You're going
to be happy again.</i>

331
00:30:53,685 --> 00:30:55,352
<i>You're going to be free.</i>

332
00:30:55,420 --> 00:30:58,522
<i>You can play forever.</i>

333
00:30:58,590 --> 00:31:00,490
With you?

334
00:31:00,558 --> 00:31:02,759
<i>Come find us, Zachary.</i>

335
00:31:08,900 --> 00:31:11,268
<i>Come find us, Zachary.</i>

336
00:31:12,837 --> 00:31:14,805
<i>We'll be waiting.</i>

337
00:31:29,554 --> 00:31:30,921
You know,
sometimes your mother and I,

338
00:31:30,989 --> 00:31:35,025
we act like mean children
on a schoolyard.

339
00:31:35,093 --> 00:31:38,362
We say things to each other
that we don't really mean,

340
00:31:38,429 --> 00:31:43,233
and you have to listen to it,
and it's not fair.

341
00:31:43,301 --> 00:31:47,938
But both of us want you to know
that we love you

342
00:31:48,006 --> 00:31:49,740
more than you can ever imagine.

343
00:31:49,807 --> 00:31:51,675
Well, what about Mommy?

344
00:31:51,743 --> 00:31:53,443
What about Mommy?

345
00:31:53,511 --> 00:31:56,313
Do you love her?

346
00:31:56,381 --> 00:31:58,782
I do.

347
00:31:58,850 --> 00:32:02,853
Well, I just don't understand
why we can't live together

348
00:32:02,921 --> 00:32:05,422
and things can be
like they used to.

349
00:32:07,992 --> 00:32:08,992
Okay.

350
00:32:12,297 --> 00:32:14,498
Because sometimes
people who love each other

351
00:32:14,565 --> 00:32:17,034
need a little time apart

352
00:32:17,101 --> 00:32:20,070
to remember why they loved
each other in the first place.

353
00:32:20,138 --> 00:32:23,874
But I promise you
I'm working on it.

354
00:32:23,942 --> 00:32:25,676
No, you're lying.

355
00:32:25,743 --> 00:32:28,278
No, sweetie.

356
00:32:28,346 --> 00:32:29,880
Yeah, you don't love her.

357
00:32:29,948 --> 00:32:33,317
- Yes, I do.
- You don't love me either.

358
00:32:33,384 --> 00:32:35,152
Claire...

359
00:32:35,219 --> 00:32:36,620
And I don't love you.

360
00:33:03,815 --> 00:33:06,216
Why doesn't anyone listen?

361
00:33:06,284 --> 00:33:09,920
We don't want a new mommy.
We want our mommy to come back

362
00:33:09,988 --> 00:33:16,026
so that things can be
like it used to be.

363
00:33:16,094 --> 00:33:19,396
You're the only one
that listens to me.

364
00:33:35,113 --> 00:33:38,949
I will never stop
loving you, ever.

365
00:33:39,017 --> 00:33:40,517
I promise.

366
00:33:40,585 --> 00:33:43,053
Cross your heart?

367
00:33:43,121 --> 00:33:44,454
Cross my heart.

368
00:33:44,522 --> 00:33:46,123
Hope to die?

369
00:33:49,293 --> 00:33:51,361
Come on, let's go home.

370
00:33:57,835 --> 00:33:59,836
Your favorite pizza.

371
00:34:01,339 --> 00:34:02,773
Here you go.

372
00:34:02,840 --> 00:34:06,343
And...

373
00:34:06,411 --> 00:34:08,945
some funny movies
to make you laugh.

374
00:34:19,757 --> 00:34:21,925
Thought I'd come by
and surprise you.

375
00:34:21,993 --> 00:34:24,995
No, no, no, I told you that
tonight is not a good night.

376
00:34:25,063 --> 00:34:27,230
Is she here?
Can I meet her?

377
00:34:29,200 --> 00:34:31,468
Oh.

378
00:34:31,536 --> 00:34:34,404
She is just adorable.

379
00:34:39,477 --> 00:34:41,211
Who are you?

380
00:34:41,279 --> 00:34:46,149
My name is Kathy.
I'm a friend of your father's.

381
00:34:46,217 --> 00:34:48,718
He never talks about you.

382
00:34:50,321 --> 00:34:55,258
- Kathy's a friend from work.
- Yeah.

383
00:34:55,326 --> 00:34:58,261
So what grade are you in,
Claire?

384
00:34:58,329 --> 00:35:00,997
Sweetheart,
someone asked you a question.

385
00:35:01,065 --> 00:35:04,267
- So?
- So why don't you answer her?

386
00:35:04,335 --> 00:35:06,303
- I don't want to.
- Jonathan...

387
00:35:06,370 --> 00:35:08,405
Claire's in third grade.

388
00:35:08,473 --> 00:35:12,375
Well, your father told me
that you like dolls.

389
00:35:12,443 --> 00:35:14,244
I brought you one.

390
00:35:16,514 --> 00:35:18,115
Isn't that nice?

391
00:35:19,550 --> 00:35:21,384
What do you say?

392
00:35:21,452 --> 00:35:22,385
It's ugly.

393
00:35:22,453 --> 00:35:25,422
No, it's not ugly.

394
00:35:25,490 --> 00:35:28,158
Yes, it is. It's ugly.
I don't want it.

395
00:35:28,226 --> 00:35:31,761
It's okay. I'm sure she'll
open up when she's ready.

396
00:35:31,829 --> 00:35:35,365
But until then, maybe she can
play with Sally, huh?

397
00:35:35,433 --> 00:35:38,869
Hey! That's crossing the line.
You pick that up right now.

398
00:35:38,936 --> 00:35:40,871
- It's just a little thing.
- Claire, now!

399
00:35:51,315 --> 00:35:53,984
That didn't go
as well as I expected.

400
00:35:56,521 --> 00:35:58,989
She just moved to Monterey,
and she left all of her friends,

401
00:35:59,056 --> 00:36:00,957
she's in a new school,

402
00:36:01,025 --> 00:36:02,826
and the separation
between Alyson and me

403
00:36:02,894 --> 00:36:05,428
is really hard on her.

404
00:36:05,496 --> 00:36:08,698
- I didn't mean to...
- Kathy...

405
00:36:08,766 --> 00:36:11,568
I told you that I needed to be
alone with my daughter tonight.

406
00:36:11,636 --> 00:36:15,672
I'm sorry. I just...

407
00:36:15,740 --> 00:36:17,307
I wanted to be with you.

408
00:36:28,352 --> 00:36:31,021
Tell you what.
I could use a drink.

409
00:36:31,088 --> 00:36:33,490
Why don't you let me
finish up these dishes?

410
00:36:33,558 --> 00:36:36,393
You go down the corner
and get us a bottle of wine.

411
00:36:36,460 --> 00:36:38,295
I really don't think
that's a good idea.

412
00:36:38,362 --> 00:36:39,963
Oh, come on.

413
00:36:40,031 --> 00:36:43,833
You really don't take no
for an answer, do you?

414
00:36:43,901 --> 00:36:46,536
Listen, you deserve
a chance to relax.

415
00:36:47,939 --> 00:36:49,472
Okay.

416
00:36:49,540 --> 00:36:52,008
And I'm gonna get some
chocolate chip ice cream

417
00:36:52,076 --> 00:36:53,310
because that's
Claire's favorite.

418
00:36:53,377 --> 00:36:55,612
- I'll be right back.
- Sure.

419
00:37:31,916 --> 00:37:37,053
<i>♪ One quiet night ♪</i>

420
00:37:37,121 --> 00:37:39,756
<i>♪ I've been waiting
oh, so long ♪</i>

421
00:37:44,061 --> 00:37:45,262
Claire?

422
00:37:49,166 --> 00:37:50,834
Claire, is that you?

423
00:38:17,762 --> 00:38:18,962
Jon?

424
00:38:22,600 --> 00:38:24,434
Jon, is that you?

425
00:39:38,175 --> 00:39:40,877
911, help me.

426
00:39:40,945 --> 00:39:43,146
<i>- 911. What's your emergency?</i>
- Oh, my God.

427
00:39:44,882 --> 00:39:46,383
<i>What's your emergency, ma'am?</i>

428
00:39:46,450 --> 00:39:48,418
<i>Ma'am?</i>

429
00:39:48,486 --> 00:39:50,153
<i>Do you need
medical assistance?</i>

430
00:39:50,221 --> 00:39:52,489
- They're here.
- <i>Ma'am, are you there?</i>

431
00:39:52,556 --> 00:39:55,191
<i>Ma'am?</i>

432
00:40:34,064 --> 00:40:35,398
- Hi.
- Hey.

433
00:40:38,969 --> 00:40:40,970
Do they know what happened?

434
00:40:41,038 --> 00:40:44,040
Said it looks like
someone broke in.

435
00:40:44,108 --> 00:40:46,109
Signs of a struggle.

436
00:40:47,645 --> 00:40:49,479
I was gone 10 minutes.

437
00:40:53,083 --> 00:40:54,717
Were you guys serious?

438
00:40:54,785 --> 00:40:56,486
No.

439
00:40:56,554 --> 00:40:58,288
She was just a friend
from work,

440
00:40:58,355 --> 00:41:00,957
but we've gone out
a couple of times.

441
00:41:01,025 --> 00:41:02,692
That's it.

442
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:04,828
Why don't you come back with us?

443
00:41:04,895 --> 00:41:07,464
I gotta stay here
and deal with the police.

444
00:41:07,531 --> 00:41:09,466
- You sure?
- Yeah.

445
00:41:09,533 --> 00:41:10,834
Why don't you and Claire
go back?

446
00:41:10,901 --> 00:41:12,569
I don't want you
anywhere around this.

447
00:41:12,636 --> 00:41:16,406
Okay. Call us
if you hear anything.

448
00:41:16,474 --> 00:41:19,175
Thanks.

449
00:41:19,243 --> 00:41:21,511
Come on, honey,
let's go get your stuff.

450
00:44:34,638 --> 00:44:36,205
Oh, God.

451
00:45:16,046 --> 00:45:17,046
Oh, my God!

452
00:45:25,622 --> 00:45:27,790
<i>You've reached Ken Stevens.
Please leave a message.</i>

453
00:45:27,858 --> 00:45:31,527
Hi, this is Alyson Simon.

454
00:45:31,595 --> 00:45:34,797
I was just calling to see
if you had put any more thought

455
00:45:34,865 --> 00:45:37,366
into the house situation.

456
00:45:37,434 --> 00:45:39,435
Could you give me a call back,
please?

457
00:45:54,685 --> 00:45:57,954
Ms. Simon?
It's Ken Stevens.

458
00:46:17,441 --> 00:46:20,009
Ms. Simon?

459
00:46:20,077 --> 00:46:21,144
It's Ken.

460
00:46:23,247 --> 00:46:26,082
I wanted to come by and clear
the air a little bit, Ms. Simon.

461
00:46:26,150 --> 00:46:28,818
I thought, uh...

462
00:46:28,886 --> 00:46:31,621
I thought we could talk about
the house's history.

463
00:46:35,392 --> 00:46:36,993
Claire?

464
00:46:38,796 --> 00:46:40,463
Is that you, honey?

465
00:46:57,414 --> 00:46:58,414
<i>Okay, yeah.
You know what?</i>

466
00:46:58,482 --> 00:47:00,249
<i>What do you want me to say?</i>

467
00:47:00,317 --> 00:47:02,552
<i>You want me to say I made
a mistake? Fine, I did.</i>

468
00:47:02,619 --> 00:47:06,322
<i>I made a mistake. You know,
I didn't call you to argue.</i>

469
00:47:06,390 --> 00:47:08,791
We gotta figure out what we're
gonna do about our daughter.

470
00:47:08,859 --> 00:47:12,628
The therapy isn't working and
I don't know what else to do.

471
00:47:12,696 --> 00:47:15,464
When she came over, she had this
spooky-looking doll with her.

472
00:47:15,532 --> 00:47:17,466
Yeah, and she won't
go anywhere without it.

473
00:47:17,534 --> 00:47:20,469
<i>She happened to mention that
Kathy brought her a new one?</i>

474
00:47:20,537 --> 00:47:22,471
What do you mean?

475
00:47:22,539 --> 00:47:24,841
<i>She brought her a new doll.</i>

476
00:47:24,908 --> 00:47:26,909
<i>I found it underneath her bed
torn apart.</i>

477
00:47:26,977 --> 00:47:30,246
<i>I'm talking violently.</i>

478
00:47:30,314 --> 00:47:32,181
- <i>Wow.</i>
- I know it's just a doll,

479
00:47:32,249 --> 00:47:34,617
but I can't help but think
it might better if it were gone.

480
00:48:08,852 --> 00:48:10,820
I'll be right back.

481
00:48:30,107 --> 00:48:31,440
Lily?

