00:53:27,771 --> 00:53:29,872
to ward off Mal de Ojo.

520
00:53:29,940 --> 00:53:32,575
Lights, please.

521
00:53:32,642 --> 00:53:35,945
Okay, well, finish the readings
on superstition for next time.

522
00:53:37,814 --> 00:53:39,748
Alyson, hi.

523
00:53:39,816 --> 00:53:42,818
I'm sorry to hear things
aren't going well with the move.

524
00:53:42,886 --> 00:53:44,720
- Oh, yeah.
- Did you bring it?

525
00:53:44,788 --> 00:53:47,189
I did.

526
00:53:47,257 --> 00:53:48,791
And it's from Guatemala?

527
00:53:48,858 --> 00:53:52,161
- Tecal.
- Hmm. It's a worry doll.

528
00:53:52,229 --> 00:53:54,129
Some people believe that when
a child has trouble sleeping,

529
00:53:54,197 --> 00:53:56,332
it's because a large amount
of stress has built up,

530
00:53:56,399 --> 00:53:57,933
but a worry doll
worries in the child's place

531
00:53:58,001 --> 00:53:59,368
so the child sleeps better.

532
00:53:59,436 --> 00:54:00,669
Does it work?

533
00:54:00,737 --> 00:54:03,072
Sometimes, but the question is

534
00:54:03,139 --> 00:54:05,374
does it work because
the doll has magical powers,

535
00:54:05,442 --> 00:54:07,876
or because the child
believes it does?

536
00:54:07,944 --> 00:54:10,946
Okay, assuming
that it does work,

537
00:54:11,014 --> 00:54:15,384
and this doll can transfer
the child's worries to itself,

538
00:54:15,452 --> 00:54:18,754
could it work
the other way around?

539
00:54:18,822 --> 00:54:23,025
I mean, could the doll transfer
something to the child?

540
00:54:23,093 --> 00:54:24,526
Look, Alyson, if your
daughter's having issues,

541
00:54:24,594 --> 00:54:25,794
I'm really not the right person.

542
00:54:25,862 --> 00:54:27,563
Okay, just look at something.

543
00:54:27,631 --> 00:54:29,498
This happened the other night.

544
00:54:29,566 --> 00:54:31,800
I picked it up.
I was trying to get rid of it,

545
00:54:31,868 --> 00:54:36,105
and now Claire has a bruise in
the exact same place on her arm.

546
00:54:36,172 --> 00:54:38,674
- It's not a voodoo doll.
- I know it's not.

547
00:54:38,742 --> 00:54:42,511
But I took this doll that night
and put it in a Dumpster,

548
00:54:42,579 --> 00:54:44,413
and the very next morning,
it was back.

549
00:54:44,481 --> 00:54:45,814
This doll.

550
00:54:45,882 --> 00:54:47,416
Yeah.

551
00:54:49,252 --> 00:54:50,853
Can you help me?

552
00:54:50,920 --> 00:54:53,155
Yeah.
If you don't mind leaving it,

553
00:54:53,223 --> 00:54:54,923
I can take a closer look at it
for you.

554
00:54:54,991 --> 00:54:57,026
You can keep it
as long as you like.

555
00:54:57,093 --> 00:54:59,595
I want this doll as far away
from my daughter as possible.

556
00:54:59,663 --> 00:55:01,330
Okay.

557
00:55:01,398 --> 00:55:02,598
Thanks.

558
00:55:06,770 --> 00:55:09,938
I want you to realize

559
00:55:10,006 --> 00:55:15,511
that as a professional who
works regularly with children,

560
00:55:15,578 --> 00:55:18,314
I have a responsibility
to report...

561
00:55:18,381 --> 00:55:22,484
suspicious behavior...

562
00:55:22,552 --> 00:55:26,322
to the authorities.

563
00:55:26,389 --> 00:55:30,859
What... What do you mean,
um, suspicious behavior?

564
00:55:32,228 --> 00:55:35,364
Tell me about her arm.

565
00:55:38,201 --> 00:55:41,337
Wait a minute. Are you...
Is that what this is about?

566
00:55:41,404 --> 00:55:43,706
Are you...

567
00:55:43,773 --> 00:55:47,676
Are you accusing me
of abusing my daughter?

568
00:55:47,744 --> 00:55:51,547
I'm giving you a chance
to explain it.

569
00:55:51,614 --> 00:55:55,017
What? Are you...

570
00:55:55,085 --> 00:55:57,119
Of course not!

571
00:55:57,187 --> 00:55:58,921
Absolutely not!

572
00:55:58,988 --> 00:56:01,290
Come sit down for a second.

573
00:56:07,731 --> 00:56:11,033
It's very important
that you help me understand

574
00:56:11,101 --> 00:56:12,901
how this happened.

575
00:56:12,969 --> 00:56:15,304
Understand what?

576
00:56:15,372 --> 00:56:17,806
She's a kid. Kids play hard.
Why don't you ask her?

577
00:56:17,874 --> 00:56:20,776
I did. She told me
that you grabbed her.

578
00:56:20,844 --> 00:56:23,712
- You lost your temper.
- I don't believe it.

579
00:56:23,780 --> 00:56:25,614
That's crazy.

580
00:56:25,682 --> 00:56:29,284
I mean, that's crazy.
Why would she tell you that?

581
00:56:29,352 --> 00:56:31,120
Do you lose your temper?

582
00:56:31,187 --> 00:56:33,021
No, I don't lose my temper!

583
00:56:33,089 --> 00:56:34,656
You're raising your voice
right now.

584
00:56:34,724 --> 00:56:36,892
Yeah, because you're making
ridiculous accusations!

585
00:56:36,960 --> 00:56:40,262
You're saying
I'm abusing my daughter.

586
00:56:40,330 --> 00:56:42,364
It's difficult
to be a single mom,

587
00:56:42,432 --> 00:56:46,201
and I can't imagine how much
stress you must be under.

588
00:56:46,269 --> 00:56:47,870
Don't you dare make this
about that.

589
00:56:51,040 --> 00:56:53,842
We'll give this one more chance,
all right?

590
00:56:53,910 --> 00:56:56,612
But if I see as much as
one bruise...

591
00:56:56,679 --> 00:57:00,315
or one scrape,

592
00:57:00,383 --> 00:57:03,552
I'll call protective services,
am I clear?

593
00:57:05,955 --> 00:57:07,489
Yeah.

594
00:57:26,609 --> 00:57:30,012
Jon, I feel like
I'm losing her,

595
00:57:30,079 --> 00:57:31,880
and I don't know
what else to do.

596
00:57:31,948 --> 00:57:34,650
<i>That's it.
I'll see you in a couple hours.</i>

597
00:57:34,717 --> 00:57:36,819
No, I can't ask you to do that.

598
00:57:36,886 --> 00:57:39,655
<i>You're not doing this alone
anymore, Alyson.</i>

599
00:57:39,722 --> 00:57:41,657
<i>I'll see you by 10:00.</i>

600
00:57:41,724 --> 00:57:43,425
Okay, thank you.

601
00:57:45,061 --> 00:57:46,428
- Hey.
- Oh!

602
00:57:48,331 --> 00:57:49,698
You scared me.

603
00:57:49,766 --> 00:57:52,034
Where's Lily?

604
00:57:52,101 --> 00:57:56,071
Why don't I take you to the
store and buy you a new doll?

605
00:57:56,139 --> 00:57:58,440
I don't want a new doll.

606
00:58:00,109 --> 00:58:02,344
I want Lily!

607
00:58:02,412 --> 00:58:04,980
Claire!

608
00:58:05,048 --> 00:58:09,718
Why do you always hurt me,
Mommy? Why?

609
00:58:09,786 --> 00:58:11,687
Oh, my God.

610
00:58:18,361 --> 00:58:20,295
Okay, let's see what we got.

611
00:58:20,363 --> 00:58:21,930
Ophelia?

612
00:58:21,998 --> 00:58:23,732
Would you like me to start
with the abdomen?

613
00:58:23,800 --> 00:58:25,601
Sounds good.

614
00:59:02,572 --> 00:59:04,773
Want me to check it out?

615
00:59:04,841 --> 00:59:08,310
No, no, I'll go.
Call maintenance and stay here.

616
00:59:39,542 --> 00:59:41,376
Hmm. Strange.

617
00:59:42,812 --> 00:59:45,213
Hello?

618
00:59:45,281 --> 00:59:47,349
Is there someone there?

619
01:00:19,215 --> 01:00:21,049
We need to get out of here.

620
01:00:24,187 --> 01:00:25,520
Ophelia?

621
01:00:29,425 --> 01:00:30,726
Ophelia?

622
01:00:56,085 --> 01:00:57,886
There's Daddy's little princess.

623
01:00:59,355 --> 01:01:01,123
I know what you want.

624
01:01:01,190 --> 01:01:04,359
Daddy's world-famous...

625
01:01:04,427 --> 01:01:06,094
flapjacks.

626
01:01:10,800 --> 01:01:13,268
- Morning.
- Morning.

627
01:01:13,336 --> 01:01:15,904
Breakfast is almost ready.
Can you get the juice?

628
01:01:15,972 --> 01:01:16,972
Yeah, sure.

629
01:01:23,112 --> 01:01:24,646
<i>The campus
has been on lockdown,</i>

630
01:01:24,714 --> 01:01:26,448
<i>as officers question anybody...</i>

631
01:01:26,516 --> 01:01:27,683
- Here you go, sweetie.
- <i>who might have information</i>

632
01:01:27,750 --> 01:01:29,451
<i>helpful to this case.</i>

633
01:01:29,519 --> 01:01:31,153
<i>The classroom
where the student was found</i>

634
01:01:31,220 --> 01:01:33,055
<i>belonged to Latin American
studies professor</i>

635
01:01:33,122 --> 01:01:34,089
<i>Elena Carranza.</i>

636
01:01:34,157 --> 01:01:36,224
Oh, my God.

637
01:01:36,292 --> 01:01:37,225
What?

638
01:01:37,293 --> 01:01:39,327
What, you knew her?

639
01:01:39,395 --> 01:01:41,029
She's the one I gave it to.

640
01:01:41,097 --> 01:01:42,998
<i>The professor was not
at her apartment.</i>

641
01:01:43,066 --> 01:01:44,533
<i>Efforts to reach her by phone
have failed.</i>

642
01:01:44,600 --> 01:01:46,234
<i>Her colleagues and students</i>

643
01:01:46,302 --> 01:01:48,704
<i>are among those being
questioned this hour...</i>

644
01:01:48,771 --> 01:01:49,771
I gotta go.

645
01:01:52,842 --> 01:01:55,577
<i>- Bill, back to you.
- Thanks, Valerie.</i>

646
01:01:55,645 --> 01:01:58,980
<i>More from this breaking story
later in our broadcast.</i>

647
01:02:03,152 --> 01:02:04,586
<i>Did your mother
do that to you?</i>

648
01:02:04,654 --> 01:02:06,221
<i>Hurt your arm?</i>

649
01:02:07,590 --> 01:02:10,492
<i>Yes.</i>

650
01:02:10,560 --> 01:02:13,328
<i>How, Claire?</i>

651
01:02:13,396 --> 01:02:15,397
<i>How did she hurt you?</i>

652
01:02:17,834 --> 01:02:20,435
<i>I was in the kitchen,</i>

653
01:02:20,503 --> 01:02:23,839
<i>and I spilled my milk,</i>

654
01:02:23,906 --> 01:02:27,142
<i>and she just...
she just finished cleaning up,</i>

655
01:02:27,210 --> 01:02:28,510
<i>and...</i>

656
01:02:31,013 --> 01:02:32,748
<i>and she got mad.</i>

657
01:02:34,884 --> 01:02:38,320
<i>Claire, I'm going to go
and get a special report</i>

658
01:02:38,387 --> 01:02:40,655
<i>so I can write this down.</i>

659
01:03:06,015 --> 01:03:07,916
I'm in the middle of something.

660
01:03:07,984 --> 01:03:11,453
I know, but someone left this
in the front door.

661
01:03:11,521 --> 01:03:14,689
It's the Simon girl's doll,
isn't it?

662
01:03:14,757 --> 01:03:16,558
- Who left it?
- Don't know.

663
01:03:16,626 --> 01:03:19,261
I went to put the mail out,
and it was just sitting there.

664
01:03:21,030 --> 01:03:24,299
Just keep it up front
for me, okay?

665
01:03:24,367 --> 01:03:25,333
Sure.

666
01:03:25,401 --> 01:03:26,868
And there's another thing.

667
01:03:26,936 --> 01:03:28,770
It's about Zachary Orcutt.

668
01:03:40,383 --> 01:03:42,150
That's a lot of blood.

669
01:03:42,218 --> 01:03:43,652
Yeah, looks like our victim
was killed up here,

670
01:03:43,719 --> 01:03:45,887
then dragged down to the desk.

671
01:03:48,391 --> 01:03:50,192
Can I help you?

672
01:03:50,259 --> 01:03:51,760
Yeah, I'm sorry,

673
01:03:51,828 --> 01:03:54,029
but Professor Carranza
was a friend of mine,

674
01:03:54,096 --> 01:03:57,699
and I'm wondering
if anyone has found a doll.

675
01:03:57,767 --> 01:03:59,501
A doll?

676
01:03:59,569 --> 01:04:01,536
Yeah, I came by, I dropped it
off with her yesterday.

677
01:04:01,604 --> 01:04:02,704
She was looking into
something for me.

678
01:04:02,772 --> 01:04:04,773
I'm gonna need you to leave.

679
01:04:04,841 --> 01:04:07,008
There's a detective outside
that'll take your statement.

680
01:04:07,076 --> 01:04:09,344
Danny, can you please
escort this woman out?

681
01:04:09,412 --> 01:04:12,013
Okay, but it's really important
that you find this doll.

682
01:04:12,081 --> 01:04:13,782
- I need you to come with me.
- Yeah, but...

683
01:04:13,850 --> 01:04:15,984
- Get her out of here.
- Yeah, okay, I'm...

684
01:04:16,052 --> 01:04:17,652
Right this way.

685
01:04:17,720 --> 01:04:19,321
Sorry.

686
01:04:19,388 --> 01:04:23,024
Anyway, they dragged her
from here to there.

687
01:04:23,092 --> 01:04:24,192
Right.
And down the steps.

688
01:04:27,096 --> 01:04:28,630
Hello?

689
01:04:28,698 --> 01:04:30,298
I really need to talk to you
about Claire.

690
01:04:30,366 --> 01:04:32,167
How soon can you get here?

691
01:04:32,235 --> 01:04:36,404
Halfway to the city is gonna
be like another hour or two.

692
01:04:36,472 --> 01:04:39,107
I know you went to see
Zachary Orcutt.

693
01:04:39,175 --> 01:04:42,444
<i>You know I evaluated him
for the court five years ago</i>

694
01:04:42,511 --> 01:04:44,512
<i>after he murdered his family.</i>

695
01:04:44,580 --> 01:04:46,248
Okay. Why are you
telling me this?

696
01:04:46,315 --> 01:04:48,683
Shortly after
you spoke with him,

697
01:04:48,751 --> 01:04:51,152
Zachary Orcutt
disappeared from his ward

698
01:04:51,220 --> 01:04:53,688
<i>and hasn't been seen since.</i>

699
01:04:56,125 --> 01:04:59,728
Are you telling me
that Claire is in danger?

700
01:04:59,795 --> 01:05:01,963
<i>Just get here
as soon as you can.</i>

701
01:05:04,500 --> 01:05:07,035
Jane, I need you to
reschedule my next...

702
01:05:52,348 --> 01:05:53,848
Claire?

703
01:05:59,822 --> 01:06:01,022
Claire.

704
01:06:07,463 --> 01:06:08,763
Sweetheart?

705
01:06:12,101 --> 01:06:13,735
Sweetheart!

706
01:06:15,738 --> 01:06:16,738
Daddy?

707
01:06:19,008 --> 01:06:20,642
Just checking.

708
01:06:50,606 --> 01:06:51,940
Claire?

709
01:06:55,811 --> 01:06:56,811
Sweetheart?

710
01:07:00,149 --> 01:07:02,417
Claire, open the door!

711
01:07:05,154 --> 01:07:06,187
Claire!

712
01:07:18,934 --> 01:07:20,268
Claire!

713
01:07:27,143 --> 01:07:28,309
Hello?

714
01:07:32,982 --> 01:07:34,649
Hello!

715
01:07:34,717 --> 01:07:35,717
Claire?

716
01:07:37,119 --> 01:07:38,686
Sweetheart?

717
01:07:45,194 --> 01:07:46,961
Claire!

718
01:07:47,029 --> 01:07:48,329
Anybody here?

719
01:08:18,494 --> 01:08:20,028
Oh, my God!

720
01:08:27,203 --> 01:08:28,603
Claire?

721
01:08:30,706 --> 01:08:32,574
Claire!

722
01:08:32,641 --> 01:08:35,009
Claire, you open this door
right now.

723
01:08:35,077 --> 01:08:36,811
Do you hear me?

724
01:08:36,879 --> 01:08:40,181
Claire, Daddy says
open this door right now!

725
01:09:01,470 --> 01:09:03,371
Sweetheart?

726
01:09:28,097 --> 01:09:30,798
There's something else in here.

727
01:09:30,866 --> 01:09:33,368
Claire, give me the doll,
sweetie.

728
01:09:33,435 --> 01:09:34,969
No.

729
01:09:35,037 --> 01:09:37,605
- Claire.
- That's it.

730
01:09:37,673 --> 01:09:40,175
No!

731
01:09:40,242 --> 01:09:41,676
Daddy!

732
01:09:41,744 --> 01:09:45,113
Jonathan!
Stop it, stop it!

733
01:09:45,181 --> 01:09:47,882
They're connected!

734
01:09:47,950 --> 01:09:49,517
Look.

735
01:09:54,890 --> 01:10:00,562
♪ Don't do you look
as the hearse goes by ♪

736
01:10:00,629 --> 01:10:04,699
- Where'd it go?
- Where is it? Where is she?

737
01:10:04,767 --> 01:10:06,367
Where is it?

738
01:10:09,605 --> 01:10:11,973
It's downstairs.
Stay here. Stay here!

739
01:10:13,609 --> 01:10:15,977
I'd run if I were you.

740
01:10:19,582 --> 01:10:21,115
Claire?

741
01:10:24,453 --> 01:10:25,820
Claire!

742
01:11:09,698 --> 01:11:11,833
Claire! Oh, my God.

743
01:11:20,509 --> 01:11:22,043
No sign of it.

744
01:11:22,111 --> 01:11:24,946
We're going now!

745
01:11:25,014 --> 01:11:27,115
Don't just stand there.
Move. Move!

746
01:11:37,793 --> 01:11:39,894
It's a prayer.
It's not getting out anymore.

747
01:11:39,962 --> 01:11:42,897
- No! No!
- Claire!

748
01:11:42,965 --> 01:11:44,666
You've got to get her
out of here!

749
01:11:44,733 --> 01:11:47,335
Let me go! Let me go!

750
01:11:47,403 --> 01:11:50,305
- Where are we going?
- Anywhere! Far from here!

751
01:11:55,577 --> 01:11:57,145
How's she doing?

752
01:11:57,212 --> 01:12:00,548
Fever still hasn't broken.

753
01:12:00,616 --> 01:12:02,417
- May I see her?
- Yeah.

754
01:12:08,357 --> 01:12:10,425
You were right.

755
01:12:10,492 --> 01:12:12,827
There's a strong connection
between Claire and the doll.

756
01:12:12,895 --> 01:12:15,396
Exactly what kind of connection
are we talking about here?

757
01:12:15,464 --> 01:12:17,632
There are three stages.

758
01:12:17,700 --> 01:12:20,568
The first stage, the doll
and the subject are introduced.

759
01:12:20,636 --> 01:12:22,236
In the second stage,

760
01:12:22,304 --> 01:12:24,439
the doll actually gets
into the host's mind.

761
01:12:24,506 --> 01:12:26,941
It influences
his or her thoughts,

762
01:12:27,009 --> 01:12:29,610
starts to change
the way they behave.

763
01:12:29,678 --> 01:12:33,181
And the third and final stage,
the doll and the host will meld.

764
01:12:33,248 --> 01:12:34,782
They'll become one.

765
01:12:34,850 --> 01:12:37,218
- Are we too late?
- I don't think so.

766
01:12:37,286 --> 01:12:39,153
But I don't think
we have much time either.

767
01:12:39,221 --> 01:12:41,189
Well, how about
if we get her to a doctor?

768
01:12:41,256 --> 01:12:43,191
There's gotta be someone
who could do something.

769
01:12:43,258 --> 01:12:46,127
It's very important that we
handle this in a specific way.

770
01:12:46,195 --> 01:12:47,962
So it is possible
to break the bond.

771
01:12:48,030 --> 01:12:50,365
I don't know. I thought if we
got your daughter far away

772
01:12:50,432 --> 01:12:51,766
that it would free her,
but I was wrong.

773
01:12:51,834 --> 01:12:53,434
The doll still has
a hold on her.

774
01:12:53,502 --> 01:12:55,236
Then I'll destroy it.

775
01:12:55,304 --> 01:12:57,705
I'll go back to the house,
and I'll destroy it.

776
01:12:57,773 --> 01:12:59,374
Jonathan...

777
01:12:59,441 --> 01:13:02,377
This time of night,
I can be there in two hours.

778
01:13:02,444 --> 01:13:03,811
You can't. You can't!

779
01:13:03,879 --> 01:13:05,680
- Do you have any children?
- No.

780
01:13:05,748 --> 01:13:07,548
Then you couldn't possibly know
what it's like to sit there

781
01:13:07,616 --> 01:13:10,318
and watch your daughter suffer
and do nothing about it.

782
01:13:10,386 --> 01:13:12,854
You're right, I can't,
but what I do know

783
01:13:12,921 --> 01:13:14,889
is that if you don't dispose
of this doll properly,

784
01:13:14,957 --> 01:13:18,092
whatever happens to that doll
will happen to your daughter.

785
01:13:18,160 --> 01:13:20,528
If the doll dies,
Claire dies.

786
01:13:20,596 --> 01:13:22,630
What is it that we need to do?
What is the proper way?

787
01:13:22,698 --> 01:13:24,532
You have to remove
the eyes first.

788
01:13:24,600 --> 01:13:26,434
If you remove the eyes
from the doll,

789
01:13:26,502 --> 01:13:28,102
the connection with Claire
should be severed.

790
01:13:28,170 --> 01:13:29,871
What do you mean, should?

791
01:13:29,938 --> 01:13:33,307
How many times do you think
I've done this?

792
01:13:33,375 --> 01:13:36,744
Okay, then that's what we'll do.

793
01:13:36,812 --> 01:13:39,781
And when were done, I'm gonna
burn the frickin' thing.

794
01:13:39,848 --> 01:13:41,582
No!

795
01:13:45,788 --> 01:13:48,523
- Come here, Claire.
- Jonathan, be careful.

796
01:13:51,493 --> 01:13:53,928
- What?
- Don't let her have it!

797
01:13:53,996 --> 01:13:55,696
You let her live!

798
01:14:00,068 --> 01:14:01,068
Jonathan!

799
01:14:02,771 --> 01:14:04,605
Oh, my God.
Where is she?

800
01:14:09,812 --> 01:14:11,512
She's outside.

801
01:14:14,249 --> 01:14:15,383
Claire!

802
01:14:18,454 --> 01:14:20,388
- Claire!
- Where is she?

803
01:14:22,591 --> 01:14:25,426
- I'll check over here.
- Okay. We'll go this way.

804
01:14:25,494 --> 01:14:27,128
Claire!

805
01:14:33,435 --> 01:14:34,735
Claire?

806
01:14:47,082 --> 01:14:49,717
Stop! Claire, stop!

807
01:14:55,224 --> 01:14:57,158
Elena!

808
01:15:20,816 --> 01:15:22,250
Elena!

809
01:15:22,317 --> 01:15:23,584
Oh, my God.

810
01:15:24,753 --> 01:15:26,153
Get the tarp!

811
01:15:43,639 --> 01:15:44,739
Okay.

812
01:15:44,806 --> 01:15:45,840
Claire.

813
01:15:51,680 --> 01:15:53,915
Elena.

814
01:15:53,982 --> 01:15:55,550
Elena?

815
01:16:20,909 --> 01:16:22,843
We're gonna be okay.

816
01:16:37,926 --> 01:16:39,193
Hold on!

817
01:16:55,644 --> 01:16:57,511
Everybody okay?

818
01:17:24,573 --> 01:17:26,574
We have to find it.

819
01:17:26,642 --> 01:17:29,243
- I'll go get it.
- You're not getting anything!

820
01:17:29,311 --> 01:17:31,012
- Claire.
- Claire!

821
01:17:53,835 --> 01:17:55,569
Claire.

822
01:17:58,140 --> 01:17:59,440
Claire.

823
01:18:09,751 --> 01:18:10,751
Oh, my...

824
01:18:16,591 --> 01:18:17,591
Sweetheart.

825
01:18:19,861 --> 01:18:21,529
Just give Daddy the doll.

826
01:18:23,131 --> 01:18:25,332
There is no doll, Daddy.

827
01:18:25,400 --> 01:18:28,903
Claire, give Daddy the doll.

828
01:18:37,546 --> 01:18:38,946
No!

829
01:18:45,821 --> 01:18:48,589
Your daughter
doesn't need you anymore,

830
01:18:48,657 --> 01:18:49,757
and neither do I.

831
01:18:51,593 --> 01:18:53,394
Alyson!

832
01:18:53,462 --> 01:18:54,729
Claire!

833
01:19:00,502 --> 01:19:01,502
Claire...

834
01:19:04,573 --> 01:19:05,840
Alyson!

835
01:19:08,410 --> 01:19:10,611
Goodbye, Mommy.

836
01:19:14,750 --> 01:19:17,184
No!

837
01:19:17,252 --> 01:19:19,086
- No!
- The eyes!

838
01:22:16,197 --> 01:22:18,499
Can I help?

839
01:22:18,566 --> 01:22:21,335
Go upstairs and bring your
mother's dresser down here.

840
01:22:21,403 --> 01:22:23,971
- You think you can handle that?
- You're funny.

841
01:22:24,039 --> 01:22:25,906
No, there's some picture frames
in the living room.

842
01:22:25,974 --> 01:22:27,241
You can grab those.

843
01:22:27,309 --> 01:22:28,609
Okay.

844
01:22:33,682 --> 01:22:36,417
- She doesn't remember anything?
- Nothing.

845
01:22:36,484 --> 01:22:40,187
I mean, she remembers moving
in here, but that's about it.

846
01:22:40,255 --> 01:22:43,223
Good.
Let's keep it that way.

847
01:22:45,894 --> 01:22:48,095
You sure about this?

848
01:22:48,163 --> 01:22:49,797
About what?

849
01:22:49,864 --> 01:22:51,498
About us.

850
01:22:51,566 --> 01:22:53,133
Yeah.

851
01:22:54,402 --> 01:22:55,836
I'm sure.

852
01:22:55,904 --> 01:22:57,171
I love you.

853
01:22:58,406 --> 01:23:00,307
I love you.

854
01:23:20,395 --> 01:23:21,562
Come on.

855
01:23:21,629 --> 01:23:23,664
Let's go home.

856
01:23:23,732 --> 01:23:25,099
Okay.

857
01:24:14,582 --> 01:24:19,787
♪ Don't you laugh
as the hearse goes by ♪

